data.sampled: time, in a faraway kingdom, there was a beautiful young princess named Ella. She was kind and compassionate, and everyone in the kingdom adored her. But one day, an evil witch cast a spell on Ella, transforming her into a hideous old woman. Determined to break the spell, Ella set out on a quest to find the one person who could help her—a famous wizard who lived in a far-off land. With the help of a brave knight, a wise old sage, and a friendly talking rabbit, Ella made her way through dangerous forests and over treacherous mountains, facing many obstacles along the way. But with every challenge she overcame, Ella grew stronger and more determined to break the spell and reclaim her true identity. Eventually, she reached the wizard's castle, where he revealed the secret to breaking the spell—all she had to do was believe in herself and never give up hope. Ella followed the wizard's instructions, and in a flash of light, she was transformed back into her beautiful self. The kingdom celebrated for days, and Ella lived happily ever after with her true love, the handsome prince. The end.
